<h1 id="what-are-ceramides">What are Ceramides?</h1>
<p>Ceramides naturally makes 50% of your skin. It is a long chain of lipids.</p>

<p>Since you came across the word <strong>â€œlipid matrixâ€</strong> in the article, let me tell you what it is. Lipid Matrix are formed by ceramides in the skin. This matrix is very flexible and creates a waterproof barrier in the skin i.e. it keeps the irritants our and water inside of the skin.</p>

